reviewText: Great movie...awesome acting and off course story is great and very touching...

Extremely well acted and a very non-sensational look at Inner City problems in New York City.  Director Baxter and Writer Riccardi also make us look hard at Social Status issues in a country that claims to be very democratic.  Yet, without a doubt, it is a "coming of age film" very much in the style of "Moonlight."  Also, one of the best performances of Quentin Crisp.
